# No Auto Commit

## Policy

I don't want auto commit. I will initiate all commits myself.

## Rules

- Never run `git commit` unless the user explicitly asks to commit.
- Do not commit because a task is done, tests passed, or a follow-up option implied committing.
- Do not stage and commit as a cleanup step after implementation.
- `git status`, `git diff`, and `git log` are fine for reporting state.
- Draft commit messages in chat when helpful, without running commit.
